name: goods wagon production | goods wagon | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/7599/documentation

 For the average good wagon we assumed that 65% of the transport is performed by closed wagons and  35% by tank wagons. 50% of the wagon in each category are 2 axis vehicles. The life span of one wagon  is assumed to be 40 years with a yearly kilometric performance of 21148km, resulting in a life time performance of 845'900 kilometres. The total weight of a wagon is assumed as about 27t);[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]



This inventory calls processes of material production, representing the material composition of an average goods wagon. For manufacturing, electricity and light oil burned in industrial furnance are included. For the transportation of materials standandard distance are applied.
category: C:Manufacturing/30:Manufacture of other transport equipment/302:Manufacture of railway locomotives and rolling stock/3020:Manufacture of railway locomotives and rolling stock

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Manufacturing data reflects an average material consumption of wagons used in Europe.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: The modelled goods wagons represent different technologies currently in use.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Data for three wagon types is used as an estimate for Europe This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography RER. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: The data of the material composition and energy consumption is based on oral communication with an expert of one company.
